The paper presents a method for anomaly detection in high-dimensional continuous data using copula functions. This method is model-based and relies on multivariate probability distributions. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), statistics (cs.ST), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
